																		It&#039;s all fun and games until somebody loses a Site
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/harryblank" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6479803); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6479803&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205383" alt="HarryBlank" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6479803)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/harryblank" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6479803); return false;" >HarryBlank</a></span> <span class="odate time_1602716882 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">14 Oct 2020 23:08</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4795779">
									

<blockquote>
<p><strong><a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-179">SCP-179</a>:</strong> (smiles) But I have no words left.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>And that is that. Team Resurrecting Resurrection, what some have wisely called BEST TEAM, has completed its storyline: Old Foes! We'd like to thank you all for kindly droppin' in.</p>
<p>TEAM RR BEST TEAM WAS: <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/karakatt" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5950867); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5950867&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1602796339" alt="KaraKatt" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5950867)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/karakatt" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5950867); return false;">KaraKatt</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/not-a-seagull" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3009022); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3009022&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1602796339" alt="not_a_seagull" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3009022)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/not-a-seagull" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3009022); return false;">not_a_seagull</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/the-pighead" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3242824); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3242824&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1602796339" alt="The Pighead" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3242824)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/the-pighead" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3242824); return false;">The Pighead</a></span>, and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/harryblank" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6479803); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6479803&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1602796339" alt="HarryBlank" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6479803)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/harryblank" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6479803); return false;">HarryBlank</a></span>. They'll be in our hearts always.</p>
<p>Thanks to&#8230; oh, what's his name, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/grigori-karpin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4558017); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4558017&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1602796339" alt="Grigori Karpin" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4558017)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/grigori-karpin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4558017); return false;">Grigori Karpin</a></span>? I think that was his name. I think that's the name of the person I talk to every single day, who's read every single thing I've posted for like a month. Thanks to that guy, for sure.</p>
<p>We had three out of four members and a canon picked out within minutes of the contest's announcement. We had four members fast, and we were hashing out our ideas from the first day to the last. Everyone contributed, and everyone was supportive. Whatever happens, we completed an arc and had a ton of fun doing so.</p>
<p>We did it, y'all. You were spectacular.</p>
